post_text:
Nolan County 4-H spot light for March ~ Vice President, John Ellis says “4-H is practical in learning skills that can be used for the rest of my life. I have enjoyed learning about shooting rifles, archery, photography, how to properly train my dog, and many textile skills. I have found new interests I never thought I would. The leadership skills I have learned as an officer, both as secretary and vice president have helped me speak in front of people with confidence.”

We are very proud of John Ellis and how he has grown in many areas through his 4-H career. Thank you John for
being such a positive influence for Nolan County 4-H.
text:
Nolan County 4-H spot light for March ~ Vice President, John Ellis says “4-H is practical in learning skills that can be used for the rest of my life. I have enjoyed learning about shooting rifles, archery, photography, how to properly train my dog, and many textile skills. I have found new interests I never thought I would. The leadership skills I have learned as an officer, both as secretary and vice president have helped me speak in front of people with confidence.”

We are very proud of John Ellis and how he has grown in many areas through his 4-H career. Thank you John for
being such a positive influence for Nolan County 4-H.

Please see below an opportunity for 4-H members in District 7 to support Hurricane Relief Efforts.
Proceeds from the purchase of shirts will be sent to the state 4-H office to go into the hurricane relief fund that has been set up.

PLEASE NOTE: If a County puts together a minimum order of 12 shirts, then their shirts can have their “COUNTYNAME” (Example: Coke County 4-H , Tom Green County 4-H, Nolan County 4-H etc.)printed on the shirt.

If you have just a few that want to order a shirt (but not meet the minimum of 12) then they will have “District 7” printed on them instead.
Contact your county extension office to place your order by September 21st.

You will also learn about daily care and health of your dog, and being a “dog foster parent.” Even community service and competition you can do with your dog. Most important of all is having fun as you build a bond with your dog and make friends who love dogs too!

May 3, 2017 at 9:41 AM ·

Learning about photography is fun! Beauty is in the eye of the camera holder!! Here participants are taught not only about the components of a camera but how to apply lighting, composition, and learning how to tell a story through photography. Participants will compete at County/District level Jr/Intermediate and Senior's compete at State level.

Do you like fashion and being creative? The 4-H Clothing and Textiles project is perfect for you. In the 4-H Clothing and Textiles Project you can learn to sew, how to be a good consumer when purchasing clothes, and the art of designing clothes and accessories, and careers in the fashion industry.
